{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b2c3d4e5-andiamo-admin-manual-only",
    "name": "Andiamo Admin Login — manual only",
    "description": "Only the two requests for a **real** login test.\n\n1. Set **`admin_email`**, **`admin_password`** (Secret), **`recaptcha_token`**. Prefer an **Environment** (dropdown top-right) so values override the empty collection defaults. Or fill the collection **Variables** tab.\n2. The POST **Pre-request** script builds JSON with `JSON.stringify` (safe for `\"` in passwords). If you type JSON in the Body tab instead, the script still merges `email` / `password` / `recaptchaToken` from that raw JSON when a variable is empty.\n3. Copy **`recaptchaToken`** from the browser Network → **Payload** (use within ~2 min). **Send** POST, then GET.\n\nCLI: `npx newman run postman/Andiamo-Admin-Login-Manual-Only.postman_collection.json --env-var admin_email=... --env-var admin_password=... --env-var recaptcha_token=...`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "https://www.andiamoevents.com" },
    { "key": "admin_email", "value": "" },
    { "key": "admin_password", "value": "" },
    { "key": "recaptcha_token", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "id": "b2c3d4e5-m001-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "name": "1 POST admin-login — real credentials",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Origin", "value": "{{baseUrl}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{admin_email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{admin_password}}\",\n  \"recaptchaToken\": \"{{recaptcha_token}}\"\n}"
        },
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/admin-login"
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "id": "b2c3d4e5-pr01-4000-8000-000000000001",
            "exec": [
              "function resolveVar(k) {",
              "  const nz = (v) => (v !== undefined && v !== null && String(v).trim() !== '' ? String(v) : '');",
              "  let v = nz(pm.environment.get(k));",
              "  if (v) return v;",
              "  v = nz(pm.collectionVariables.get(k));",
              "  if (v) return v;",
              "  v = nz(pm.globals.get(k));",
              "  if (v) return v;",
              "  try {",
              "    if (typeof pm.variables !== 'undefined' && pm.variables.get) {",
              "      v = nz(pm.variables.get(k));",
              "      if (v) return v;",
              "    }",
              "  } catch (e) {}",
              "  return '';",
              "}",
              "let email = resolveVar('admin_email');",
              "let password = resolveVar('admin_password');",
              "let recaptchaToken = resolveVar('recaptcha_token');",
              "try {",
              "  const raw0 = pm.request && pm.request.body && pm.request.body.raw;",
              "  if (typeof raw0 === 'string' && raw0.trim().charAt(0) === '{') {",
              "    const p = JSON.parse(raw0);",
              "    if (p && typeof p === 'object') {",
              "      if (!email && p.email != null) email = String(p.email);",
              "      if (!password && p.password != null) password = String(p.password);",
              "      if (!recaptchaToken && p.recaptchaToken != null) recaptchaToken = String(p.recaptchaToken);",
              "    }",
              "  }",
              "} catch (e) {}",
              "pm.request.body.update({",
              "  mode: 'raw',",
              "  raw: JSON.stringify({",
              "    email: email || '',",
              "    password: password || '',",
              "    recaptchaToken: recaptchaToken || '',",
              "  }),",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "id": "b2c3d4e5-s01-4000-8000-000000000001",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "  pm.test('Login success', () => pm.response.json().success === true);",
              "  pm.test('Admin object returned', () => !!pm.response.json().admin);",
              "} else if (pm.response.code === 401) {",
              "  pm.test('Invalid credentials', () => pm.response.json().error === 'Invalid credentials');",
              "} else if (pm.response.code === 400) {",
              "  pm.test('Bad request', () => !!pm.response.json().error);",
              "} else if (pm.response.code === 429) {",
              "  pm.test('Rate limited', () => true);",
              "} else {",
              "  pm.test('Unexpected status ' + pm.response.code, () => false);",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "b2c3d4e5-m002-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "name": "2 GET verify-admin — after login",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [{ "key": "Origin", "value": "{{baseUrl}}" }],
        "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/verify-admin"
      },
      "response": [],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "id": "b2c3d4e5-s02-4000-8000-000000000001",
            "exec": [
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "  const j = pm.response.json();",
              "  pm.test('Session valid', () => j.valid === true);",
              "  pm.test('Has admin', () => !!j.admin);",
              "} else {",
              "  pm.test('Not authenticated', () => [401, 403].includes(pm.response.code));",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
